File: Anti-apartheid activist Neil Aggett died suspiciously in detention in 1982. JOHANNESBURG - It's been fourty years since his death, and now the inquest finding into activist Neil Aggett’s death has been overturned. The high court in Johannesburg handed down its ruling today following an application to overturn the apartheid-era inquest that found Aggett committed suicide while in police custody. Judge Motsamai Makume says Aggett's death was not a suicide. Makume says the 1982 inquest was a cover-up. Watch the recorded court proceedings below. 40 years after his death, the inquest finding into activist Neil Aggett’s death may be overturned. The 1982 inquest concluded that Aggett committed suicide while in police detention. Families of many fallen freedom fighters have been fighting for years to have the law pursue justice for their loved ones.